Prerequisite:- A working docker environment in Linux.

chmod +x build.sh
./build.sh <gobgp image tag> Dockerfile2
Note: Use sudo for the above command, if required.

example:-
sudo ./build.sh apr23 Dockerfile2

Checking the basic bgp peering status:-

$ sudo docker exec -ti bgp1 gobgp global
AS:        65001
Router-ID: 172.18.0.2
Listening Port: 179, Addresses: 0.0.0.0, ::
$ sudo docker exec -ti bgp1 gobgp neighbor
Peer          AS  Up/Down State       |#Received  Accepted
172.18.0.3 65001 00:00:12 Establ      |        0         0
